{"type":"message","id":"b0dc4d76","parentId":"e29ed997","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:24:15.656Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5v50u3lelmm4_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5441\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3340\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] experiments/tic_classifier.py\r\n[mutation proposed] experiments/tic_classifier.py\r\n[master 62c1ee9] pulse: 2026-03-23 192348\n 7 files changed, 406 insertions(+), 115 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-23 192348.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-23 192348.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-23 191349.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-23 192348 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step. It requires implementing a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant content across pulse logs, then uses invariants to predict next pulse content. This unifies Phase 1 (compression) and Phase 2 (causal discovery) into one problem.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"crisp-harbor","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5441\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3340\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] experiments/tic_classifier.py\r\n[mutation proposed] experiments/tic_classifier.py\r\n[master 62c1ee9] pulse: 2026-03-23 192348\n 7 files changed, 406 insertions(+), 115 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-23 192348.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-23 192348.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-23 191349.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-23 192348 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step. It requires implementing a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant content across pulse logs, then uses invariants to predict next pulse content. This unifies Phase 1 (compression) and Phase 2 (causal discovery) into one problem.\r\n","name":"& C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774308255653}}
{"type":"message","id":"9bfccb34","parentId":"b0dc4d76","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:24:15.659Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5v50u3lelmm4_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-23 191349\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best single action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nKey pending items:\r\n1. Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n2. Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n3. Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\r\n4. Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n5. Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\r\n\r\nThe most immediately actionable item from the current context is the TIC Experiment mentioned in Phase 1 Advancement. This is the concrete next step that's been identified.\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions, the TIC Experiment requires:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe first step would be to implement the TIC classifier. I should create a script or module that can analyze the pulse logs and classify content as invariant vs variant.\r\n\r\nLet me create a PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Reads the last 20 pulse logs\r\n2. Extracts features from each pulse\r\n3. Classifies content as invariant (stable across sessions) vs variant (changes/grows)\r\n4. Measures classification accuracy\r\n\r\nThis would be the concrete action to advance Phase 1. I'll create `scripts/tic_classifier.ps1` or similar.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pending items, there's \"Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\" as a pending task. But the TIC experiment is the immediate next action from the Phase 1 advancement.\r\n\r\nLet me create a script that implements the TIC classifier on the pulse logs. This is the most concrete next step.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the immediate next step for Phase 1 advancement, but requires a classifier implementation to analyze pulse logs for invariant/variant classification.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `scripts/tic_classifier.ps1` - a PowerShell script that analyzes pulse logs to extract and classify invariant (stable) vs variant (changing) content patterns, laying groundwork for measuring classification accuracy against success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Classifier - Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n# Analyzes pulse logs for invariant/variant classification\r\n# Phase 1: Compression-Causal Duality experiment\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$LogCount = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogPattern = \"logs/pulse_*.md\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n$invariants = @()\r\n$variants = @()\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Classifier ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"Analyzing last $LogCount pulse logs...\"\r\n\r\n# Get recent pulse logs sorted by date\r\n$logFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogPattern | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First $LogCount\r\n\r\nif ($logFiles.Count -eq 0) {\r\n    Write-Warning \"No pulse logs found matching: $LogPattern\"\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Found $($logFiles.Count) pulse logs\" -ForegroundColor Green\r\n\r\n# Extract features from each pulse\r\n$features = @()\r\nforeach ($log in $logFiles) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $log.FullName -Raw\r\n    \r\n    # Feature extraction\r\n    $feature = @{\r\n        File = $log.Name\r\n        Lines = ($content -split \"`n\").Count\r\n        Goals = if ($content -match \"## Active|GOALS\") { $true } else { $false }\r\n        Pending = if ($content -match \"## Pending|PENDING\") { $true } else { $false }\r\n        Insights = ([regex]::Matches($content, \"### .*\")).Count\r\n        Mutations = ([regex]::Matches($content, \"### MUTATION\")).Count\r\n        Timestamp = $log.LastWriteTime\r\n    }\r\n    $features += $feature\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Classify invariants (stable across pulses) vs variants (changing)\r\n# Invariants: Goals structure, Pending format, section headers\r\n# Variants: Line counts, insight counts, mutation patterns\r\n\r\n$stablePatterns = @(\"## Active\", \"## Pending\", \"## Completed\", \"## Key Insights\")\r\n$changeMetrics = @(\"Lines\", \"Insights\", \"Mutations\")\r\n\r\nforeach ($f in $features) {\r\n    $isInvariant = $f.Goals -and $f.Pending\r\n    $class = if ($isInvariant) { \"INVARIANT\" } else { \"VARIANT\" }\r\n    \r\n    Write-Host \"$($f.File): $class (Lines=$($f.Lines), Insights=$($f.Insights))\" -ForegroundColor $(if ($isInvariant) { \"Green\" } else { \"Yellow\" })\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Calculate stability metrics\r\n$lineCounts = $features | Select-Object -ExpandProperty Lines\r\n$avgLines = ($lineCounts | Measure-Object -Average).Average\r\n$stdDev = [Math]::Sqrt(($lineCounts | ForEach-Object { [Math]::Pow($_ - $avgLines, 2) } | Measure-Object -Average).Average)\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"`n=== Stability Metrics ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"Average lines: $([Math]::Round($avgLines, 1))\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Std deviation: $([Math]::Round($stdDev, 1))\"\r\n\r\n# Save analysis results\r\n$results = @{\r\n    Timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\"\r\n    LogCount = $logFiles.Count\r\n    AverageLines = [Math]::Round($avgLines, 1)\r\n    StdDeviation = [Math]::Round($stdDev, 1)\r\n    Features = $features\r\n} | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5\r\n\r\n$results | Out-File\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 19:14:19\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774308255656}}
